Subject: SCP-9386 
Date: 12/10/2012 
Director Ezekial,
As of today, the Site has gone two weeks without experiencing a single containment breach from SCP-9386, a record we had not reached for almost three years. As per our tentative agreement regarding Dr. Langstrum's proposed containment plan, this may prove her theory that a joint-containment solution could be the most effective form of preventing further breaches. 
Coincidentally, as I know you're aware, the Department of Ornithology has recently finished construction of the Cohabitive Avian Terrarium and have already successfully introduced several of our onsite anomalies into the enclosure. While I know you have your concerns with both SCP-9386 and the CAT, I believe this would be the easiest and most cost-efficient way of attempting joint-containment. 
Let me know how you'd with to proceed. 
Sincerely, 
- Doctor Lisa Ernest 
Site Director of Containment 
